<gco:CharacterString>Densities of the code goby Gobiosoma robustum Ginsburg and clown goby Microgobius gulosus (Girard) vary across regions of Florida Bay. Although their distributions overlap to a limited degree, G. robustum is found in great abundance in the seagrass beds of the western and southern portion of the bay, where a strong Gulf of Mexico influence maintains salinities at a relatively constant level (35-40 ppt). Conversely, M. gulosus is most common in the north-eastern section of the bay that is influenced by freshwater inflow and generally is characterised by lower salinities and sparse submerged vegetation.</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:abstract>          <gmd:purpose>             <gco:CharacterString>To examine the effects of salinity, habitat complexity, competition, and susceptibility to predation as possible factors underlying the distribution of these two species.</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:purpose>          <gmd:status>             <gmd:MD_ProgressCode
